	Alternative{lang='ka.', text='devā'}}
 devakāyā, <alternatives><alternative lang="vri">cavate</alternative><alternative lang="ka.">cavanti</alternative></alternatives> 
Note { id=9, line='84', referenceLine='116', original='cavanti (ka.)', type='auto', previous=' devakāyā, cavate '
	Alternative{lang='vri', text='cavate'}
	Alternative{lang='ka.', text='cavanti'}}
āyusaṅkhayā;</gatha1>
<gathalast line="117">Tayo saddā niccharanti, devānaṃ anumodataṃ.</gathalast>
<hangnum line="118" number="35"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="119">‘Ito bho sugatiṃ gaccha, manussānaṃ sahabyataṃ;</gatha1>
<gathalast line="120">Manussabhūto saddhamme, labha saddhaṃ anuttaraṃ.</gathalast>
<hangnum line="121" number="36"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="122">‘‘‘Sā te saddhā niviṭṭhāssa, mūlajātā patiṭṭhitā;</gatha1>
<gathalast line="123">Yāvajīvaṃ asaṃhīrā, saddhamme suppavedite.</gathalast>
<hangnum line="124" number="37"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="125">‘‘‘Kāyena <pageBreak edition="M" number="1.0217" /><pageBreak edition="P" number="1.0195" />kusalaṃ katvā, vācāya kusalaṃ bahuṃ;</gatha1>
<gathalast line="126">Manasā kusalaṃ katvā, <alternatives><alternative lang="vri">abyāpajjaṃ</alternative><alternative lang="syā.">abyāpajjhaṃ</alternative><alternative lang="itivuttake 83">appamāṇaṃ</alternative></alternatives> 
Note { id=10, line='93', referenceLine='126', original='abyāpajjhaṃ (syā.), appamāṇaṃ (itivuttake 83)', type='auto', previous='Manasā kusalaṃ katvā, abyāpajjaṃ '
	Alternative{lang='vri', text='abyāpajjaṃ'}
	Alternative{lang='syā.', text='abyāpajjhaṃ'}
	Alternative{lang='itivuttake 83', text='appamāṇaṃ'}}
nirūpadhiṃ.</gathalast>
<hangnum line="127" number="38"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="128">‘‘‘Tato opadhikaṃ puññaṃ, katvā dānena taṃ bahuṃ;</gatha1>
<gathalast line="129">Aññepi macce saddhamme, brahmacariye nivesaya’.</gathalast>
<hangnum line="130" number="39"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="131">‘‘Imāya anukampāya, devā devaṃ yadā vidū;</gatha1>
<gathalast line="132">Cavantaṃ anumodanti, ehi deva punappunaṃ 
Note { id=11, line='103', referenceLine='132', original='devapuraṃ puna (syā.)', type='auto', previous='Cavantaṃ anumodanti, ehi deva punappunaṃ '
	Alternative{lang='vri', text='deva punappunaṃ'}
	Alternative{lang='syā.', text='devapuraṃ puna'}}
.</gathalast>
<hangnum line="133" number="40"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="134"><note>saṃviggohaṃ (syā.)</note>tadā āsi, devasaṅghe samāgate;</gatha1>
<gathalast line="135">Kaṃsu nāma ahaṃ yoniṃ, gamissāmi ito cuto.</gathalast>
<hangnum line="136" number="41"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="137">‘‘Mama <pageBreak edition="V" number="1.0201" />saṃvegamaññāya, samaṇo bhāvitindriyo;</gatha1>
<gathalast line="138">Mamuddharitukāmo so, āgacchi mama santikaṃ.</gathalast>
<hangnum line="139" number="42"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="140">‘‘Sumano nāma nāmena, padumuttarasāvako;</gatha1>
<gathalast line="141">Atthadhammānusāsitvā, saṃvejesi mamaṃ tadā.</gathalast>
<hangnum line="142" number="43"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="143">‘‘Tassāhaṃ <pageBreak edition="T" number="1.0288" />vacanaṃ sutvā, buddhe cittaṃ pasādayiṃ;</gatha1>
<gathalast line="144">Taṃ dhīraṃ abhivādetvā, tattha kālaṃkato ahaṃ.</gathalast>
<hangnum line="145" number="44"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="146"><note>upapajjissaṃ (sī.)</note>tattheva, sukkamūlena codito;</gatha1>
<gathalast line="147">Kappānaṃ satasahassaṃ, duggatiṃ nupapajjahaṃ.</gathalast>
<hangnum line="148" number="45"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="149">‘‘Paṭisambhidā catasso…pe… kataṃ buddhassa sāsanaṃ’’.</gatha1>
<paragraph line="150">Itthaṃ sudaṃ āyasmā ekacintiko thero imā gāthāyo abhāsitthāti.</paragraph>
<centered line="151">Ekacintikattherassāpadānaṃ sattamaṃ.</centered>
<subhead line="152">8. Tikaṇṇipupphiyattheraapadānaṃ</subhead>
<hangnum line="153" number="46"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="154">‘‘Devabhūto ahaṃ santo, accharāhi purakkhato;</gatha1>
<gathalast line="155">Pubbakammaṃ saritvāna, buddhaseṭṭhaṃ anussariṃ.</gathalast>
<hangnum line="156" number="47"></hangnum>
<gatha1 line="157"> ‘‘<alternatives><alternative lang="vri">Tikaṇṇipupphaṃ</alternative><alternative lang="ka.">kiṃkaṇipupphaṃ</alternative></alternatives> 
